{"id":8088,"date":"2017-11-04T00:35:18","date_gmt":"2017-11-04T07:35:18","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=8088"},"modified":"2024-01-06T21:19:56","modified_gmt":"2024-01-07T05:19:56","slug":"mount-jardine","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/11\/04\/mount-jardine\/","title":{"rendered":"MOUNT JARDINE"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><em><strong>Mt JARDINE<\/strong><\/em> 2442m. \u00a08000&#8242;<br \/>\n<\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>Follow a historic mining trail to a high alpine ridge and summit. Views are of the Valley of Ghosts.<\/em>\u00a0<em>This has been a rare climb for the Kootenay Mountaineering Club &#8211; last mentioned as a winter ski in 1992.\u00a0<\/em><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"border: none;\">Called Empire, in the winter, this area is the prime snowmobiling location around Kaslo. They mostly go on the Blue Ridge FSR that parallels the highway for several kilometres and can be accessed from either end \u2013 at Buchanan Lookout Road or at Ten Mile Creek Road.\u00a0<\/span><span style=\"border: none;\">Ten Mile has a large highway pull-off area that forms a great staging area for the snowmobilers and their trucks and trailers.<\/span><\/em><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Rating: \u2666\u2666\u2666\u2666\u25ca<br \/>\nLocation:<\/strong> West of Kaslo north of Highway 31A in the Goat Range.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> D2 strenuous \u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Elevation Gain:<\/strong> +1245m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Key Elevations:<\/strong> Trailhead: 1197 m, Summit Mt Jardine 2442m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong>\u00a0<\/span>6.6 km one way<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 6-7 hours return <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> July to early October <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong> 4WD high clearance for water bars in the last .5 km. \u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82K\/3<\/span><\/p>\n<p><strong>Drive.<\/strong> From Kaslo, take Highway 31A towards New Denver and the Rossiter FSR.<br \/>\n<strong>0.0 km. <\/strong>Ascend for 1.0km passing the Wagon Road and switchback left.<br \/>\n2.4 km. Junction. The left goes to the\u00a0Lyle Lakes\/Mt Brennan trailhead. Right goes to Mt Jardine.<br \/>\n2.5 km. Fork right and cross deep water bars requiring 4WD high clearance.<br \/>\n3.0 km. Park at a wide pullout on the right. Further is a washout<\/p>\n<p><strong>Route\/Trail.<\/strong> Walk up the road through a large washout.<br \/>\n0.8km. The signed <strong>Beaver Mine Trai<\/strong>l is on the left. The Beaver Mine was staked in 1891. Ascend on switchbacks through an old clearcut into the forest and switchback steadily up to the ridge.<br \/>\n3 km. Views are far below and to the ridge from Mt Jardine.<br \/>\n4.7 km. The trail ends after 2 hours. An old route that heads straight north is blocked off by logs. Take the new route right (east) on a hiker-made trail gradually climbing to the basin below Mount Jardine. Flagging tape marks the way.<br \/>\nPass old diggings and tailing piles of the Beaver Claim but there is no mine. Reach the ridge and cross NE across the basin under Mt Jardine to the low point on the west ridge of the mountain. Walk up the long grassy slope to the steep final ascent. Sign the register.<br \/>\nTexas and Reco are to the south with Kokanee Glacier far away. Mount Brennan is NW with Whitewater Mountain beyond. Blue Ridge and Mt Buchanan are to the east.<br \/>\n<strong><em>Return<\/em><\/strong> the same way &#8211; 2.5 hours.<\/p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">References: <\/span><\/strong><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/westkootenayhiking.ca\/mt-jardine\/\">https:\/\/westkootenayhiking.ca\/mt-jardine\/<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Mt JARDINE 2442m. \u00a08000&#8242; Follow a historic mining trail to a high alpine ridge and summit. Views are of the Valley of Ghosts.\u00a0This has been a rare climb for the Kootenay Mountaineering Club &#8211; last mentioned as a winter ski &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/11\/04\/mount-jardine\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-8088","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-